[{"id":"VR802584","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a particle and two parallel plates that are oriented horizontally. The upper plate is positively charged and the lower plate is negatively charged. The particle has a charge of positive q and moves at velocity v toward the right and toward the top of the page midway between the two plates. Between the two parallel plates there is a magnetic field directed into the page of magnitude B.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR802584.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A positively charged particle is traveling within a capacitor, as shown. Between the plates of the capacitor, there is an external magnetic field directed into the page. Which of the following shows a possible direction for the sum of forces on the positively charged particle? Gravitational effects can be ignored.</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR802584_rubric","choicesHtml":["<div class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a vertical arrow pointing up.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR802584.g02.svg\"/></div>","<div class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a vertical arrow pointing down.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR802584.g03.svg\"/></div>","<div class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a horizontal arrow pointing to the right.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR802584.g04.svg\"/></div>","<div class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a horizontal arrow pointing to the left.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR802584.g05.svg\"/></div>"],"answer":3}]